    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A black pigment prepared from burnt animal bones mixed with water and glue then formed into lumps or drops; was commercially sold as pellets, used in the 18th and 19th century for house paint.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
